        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 5:28PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rockingham, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Maxton, Hoffman, Ellerbe,
Dobbins Heights, Wagram, and Gibson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
